Now I have a complete picture. Here is the comprehensive analysis:

---

## 1. What `rpc.client.list.queryOptions` Returns

**File:** `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/rpc/router/client.ts`

The `clientList` procedure is defined as:

```ts
export const clientList = protectedProcedure
  .meta({ permission: { action: "read", resource: "clients" } })
  .input(listClientsSchema)                       // Zod input schema
  .handler(async ({ input, context }) => {
    const result = await listClients({ ... });
    return result;
  });
```

There is **no `.output()` schema** on any procedure in this codebase. The output type is inferred from the handler's return value. The `listClients` service function (`/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/services/client-service.ts`, line 200-289) returns:

```ts
{
  items: Array<{
    archived: boolean;
    assigneeId: string;
    assigneeImage: string | null;
    assigneeName: string | null;
    createdAt: Date | null;
    id: number;
    legalName: string | null;
    logo: string | null;
    name: string;
    slug: string;
    updatedAt: Date | null;
    assignee: {
      id: string;
      image: string | null;
      name: string | null;
    };
  }>;
  nextCursor: string | null;
}
```

The `queryOptions()` return type (from oRPC's `ProcedureUtils<TClientContext, TInput, TOutput, TError>`) is:

```ts
queryOptions<U, USelectData = TOutput>(
  ...rest: MaybeOptionalOptions<U & QueryOptionsIn<TClientContext, TInput, TOutput, TError, USelectData>>
): NoInfer<U & Omit<QueryOptionsBase<TOutput, TError>, keyof U>>
```

Where `QueryOptionsBase<TOutput, TError>` includes:

```ts
{
  queryKey: DataTag<QueryKey, TOutput, TError>;
  queryFn: QueryFunction<TOutput>;
  // ...
}
```

So `rpc.client.list.queryOptions(...)` returns an object whose `queryKey` is `DataTag<QueryKey, ClientListOutput, Error>`, enabling TanStack Query to infer `data` as the `ClientListOutput` type shown above.

---

